Japan will ratify the 1986 InternationalCocoa Agreement (ICCA), with effect from July 1, and will renewits membership in the International Cocoa Organisation (ICCO),Foreign Affairs Ministry officials said.    They said Japan would participate in an ICCO meeting onJuly 13 in London to revise ICCO buffer stock policy.    The 1986 ICCA has been in effect since January 1987.    Government approval to participate in the ICCO was delayedby parliamentary debate over the sales tax issue, the officialssaid. REUTER&#3;